1
00:00:00,083 --> 00:00:07,500
The solitary cell is a meter and a half
wide and about two and a half meters long

2
00:00:08,208 --> 00:00:15,541
It has a toilet and two mattresses.
Sometimes they put two or three people in it

3
00:00:15,791 --> 00:00:18,958
They keep them in it for two
or three days then move them

4
00:00:19,916 --> 00:00:27,458
After that they take them away from me, and I would have gotten to know
them. Among them, as I told you, was Hajj Walid from the village of Hamam

5
00:00:27,958 --> 00:00:34,125
And among them was Abu Yousuf, a
vegetable seller in the first neighborhood

6
00:00:34,791 --> 00:00:38,750
And Ali al-Wudaihi, I spoke
with him through the wall

7
00:00:39,041 --> 00:00:44,458
And there was Ammar from
Mansoura, his name was Ammar al-Raji

8
00:00:48,166 --> 00:00:54,875
And there was Hammadi al-Aziz from
Musheirfa, and Fattouh was with him

9
00:00:58,416 --> 00:01:03,833
And another young man whose name I
forgot, because it has been a long time

10
00:01:04,625 --> 00:01:12,000
These are the people I knew. Also
Hayel al-Ghadban was with me there

11
00:01:12,333 --> 00:01:15,708
I do not know, and they do not
tell you why they put you in solitary

12
00:01:16,375 --> 00:01:21,833
You cannot say a single word. They put you
here and that is it, you must stay silent

13
00:01:21,833 --> 00:01:25,833
Of course they put cameras here, in
every solitary cell they put a camera

14
00:01:27,083 --> 00:01:32,500
The barrier between the area where you sit and the
toilet is a sheet, a cloth cover used as a divider

15
00:01:32,958 --> 00:01:38,958
Of course there are no nails in the wall, just
two mattresses, two pillows, and two blankets

16
00:01:40,125 --> 00:01:47,500
The weather was very hot. There is a vent, and something strange
happened inside the prison. I heard about it from the commotion

17
00:01:47,833 --> 00:01:52,333
Someone escaped from inside the prison, even
though it seemed impossible for anyone to escape

18
00:01:52,916 --> 00:01:55,958
After that they brought welders. We could hear
the sound of welding and they started welding

19
00:01:56,750 --> 00:02:03,458
He escaped from the group cells. He prepared a
spot and escaped from it, and managed to get away

20
00:02:04,250 --> 00:02:10,583
As for the solitary cells, there is nothing in them
but this window, and it is reinforced with iron

21
00:02:11,291 --> 00:02:19,250
They welded iron bars onto it. It is impossible to think
about getting out. There is absolutely no way to escape

22
00:02:19,958 --> 00:02:23,791
I spent my time in the solitary cell sitting,
and when it was time for prayer I prayed

23
00:02:24,875 --> 00:02:31,416
We spent most of the time eating. The food was mostly canned
goods like mortadella and other things. We opened the cans and ate

24
00:02:32,000 --> 00:02:37,958
And whoever was imprisoned with me, I listened to his story. He
told me what happened to him, and each person had a different story

25
00:02:38,708 --> 00:02:42,708
We kept each other company, because the
situation was boring and prison was hard

26
00:02:43,250 --> 00:02:46,791
You live in fear and try to distract yourself
because you believe you will be executed tomorrow

27
00:02:47,166 --> 00:02:51,000
There is no hope of getting out. If you entered
this place it seemed impossible to leave

28
00:02:51,583 --> 00:02:56,708
Of course during that time, a masked
person would come and mock us

29
00:02:57,125 --> 00:03:05,500
He would point his pistol at us and say, I will kill you, or tomorrow you will be executed,
or tomorrow morning they will take you to the roundabout for execution, to intimidate us

30
00:03:05,583 --> 00:03:11,250
And during that period we believed everything we heard.
We did not expect that what they said could be a lie

31
00:03:11,333 --> 00:03:17,041
Or that it would not happen to us. But every person was
exposed to anything, based on the torture I saw and heard about

32
00:03:17,875 --> 00:03:22,708
Interviewer: What did you do inside
the cell, any games or anything?

33
00:03:22,791 --> 00:03:30,458
We could not do anything. There were very fine pebbles we picked
from the wall. I tried with some of them but they refused to play

34
00:03:30,583 --> 00:03:34,208
It became routine for us. We will die?
No problem, we are already like the dead

35
00:03:34,333 --> 00:03:37,041
Interviewer: Tell us about the
game you used to play, what was it?

36
00:03:37,375 --> 00:03:46,583
A game where we moved a stone like this, to
entertain ourselves. It was not really a game

37
00:03:46,916 --> 00:03:50,416
The point was to kill
time, to make it pass faster

38
00:03:52,041 --> 00:03:58,583
From here we could hear the call to prayer. They had someone
with a beautiful voice when he called the prayer, we heard him

39
00:03:58,791 --> 00:04:03,666
We knew it was afternoon or midday prayer, but we could
not see daylight. We wished we could see the light

40
00:04:04,583 --> 00:04:09,916
When they took us out of the prison and on the road
removed the blindfold from our eyes, I felt dizzy

41
00:04:10,583 --> 00:04:15,791
My friend and I had not seen the sun for 33
days. We had no idea what was happening

42
00:04:16,333 --> 00:04:18,791
Interviewer: Tell us about
the meals, what were they like?

43
00:04:18,875 --> 00:04:24,541
As for meals, one time
someone brought me a rice dish

44
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:34,166
Stuffed eggplant with rice. He gave me three pieces,
knowing that I was known among them for loving food

45
00:04:34,541 --> 00:04:39,333
Since we were smokers and there were no
cigarettes, our appetite for food increased a lot

46
00:04:40,291 --> 00:04:46,125
They brought me canned meat,
cheese cubes, bread, jam, and halva

47
00:04:46,583 --> 00:04:50,500
Boiled potatoes, tomatoes,
and cucumbers, things like that

48
00:04:50,916 --> 00:04:54,958
Cooking and hot meals were only
for the group cells, from what I heard

49
00:04:55,458 --> 00:05:02,500
Tea in a plastic cup, poured for me when I asked. Sometimes
I asked and they gave it, and sometimes they did not

50
00:05:03,083 --> 00:05:06,666
Sometimes he would call me
and say, take this, drink your tea

51
00:05:07,833 --> 00:05:13,791
The group cells were different. Tea and food whenever we wanted.
In the solitary cell I only had whatever food they gave me

52
00:05:14,583 --> 00:05:17,333
Interviewer: Was food served on a
regular schedule, breakfast, lunch, dinner?

53
00:05:17,416 --> 00:05:21,750
The food was organized. And for the sick,
they brought medicine and gave it to them

54
00:05:21,958 --> 00:05:27,750
For example, you tell them you have a throat infection and need
anti-inflammatory pills. They give you the medicine, they bring it

55
00:05:29,833 --> 00:05:34,541
Nail clippers, if I asked he gave them
to me. He stood there watching me

56
00:05:35,125 --> 00:05:38,250
When I finished trimming, he took the
clippers back and left, closing the door

57
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:42,208
Of course there is a small hatch in the
door, a black door with a small opening

58
00:05:42,208 --> 00:05:43,916
I knock on the door, he opens
the hatch and asks what I want

59
00:05:44,541 --> 00:05:50,500
But if he wants to take you to interrogation, he opens the hatch and
tells you, get ready, come out and put the blindfold on your eyes

60
00:05:50,583 --> 00:05:55,041
Or he makes you face the wall, puts the
blindfold on you himself, and takes you out

61
00:05:56,125 --> 00:06:00,416
Interviewer: How many people were with you?
And what were the charges brought against them?

62
00:06:00,833 --> 00:06:05,000
The charges were varied. Each
person had a different charge

63
00:06:05,166 --> 00:06:11,916
One person was charged with being Free Syrian Army, another
charged with communicating with the popular committees, and another

64
00:06:12,458 --> 00:06:22,291
Was charged with taking money to smuggle people.
People had different charges, each person had a story

65
00:06:23,708 --> 00:06:28,791
Most of the older people they brought
in were between 50 and 55 years old

66
00:06:29,375 --> 00:06:34,375
Of course all of their charges were related
to dealing with the popular committees

67
00:06:35,041 --> 00:06:42,791
Or they had relatives in the popular committees and were
arrested on charges that their relative was in contact with them

68
00:06:44,708 --> 00:06:48,541
Interviewer: Did they prevent
you from talking inside the cell?

69
00:06:49,458 --> 00:06:53,041
Yes, they prevented you. You are not
allowed to talk, unless you needed something

70
00:06:55,250 --> 00:07:01,500
They prevented us from talking a lot. If you talked
too much you would be tortured and humiliated

71
00:07:02,458 --> 00:07:06,166
They take you out for interrogation,
for example, and torture you on the hoist

72
00:07:06,500 --> 00:07:10,958
Just the mention of the hoist and you go silent
automatically. There is no reason to talk

73
00:07:11,625 --> 00:07:18,125
Interviewer: How many
ISIS members did you see?

74
00:07:18,166 --> 00:07:24,333
During interrogation I saw four people: the
guard, the interrogator, and two others with him

75
00:07:24,375 --> 00:07:28,083
These two assisted in the torture.
Other than that we did not see anyone

76
00:07:28,625 --> 00:07:30,125
Interviewer: What
were their names?

77
00:07:30,708 --> 00:07:37,458
They did not have names, just noms de guerre like
Abu so-and-so. Each person had a nom de guerre

78
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:43,625
Like Abu Islam. Of course he was the
guard. And with him was a Saudi person

79
00:07:43,666 --> 00:07:50,791
I said to him, you are Saudi. He scolded me
and said, I am from the Arabian Peninsula

80
00:07:51,166 --> 00:07:58,041
They called him Abu Safwan and he
was Saudi. The interrogator was Abu Usama

81
00:07:58,083 --> 00:08:05,916
We would call him Abu Usama. He would say, I am not Abu Usama,
and did not give us a name. That is all that happened with me

82
00:08:08,250 --> 00:08:11,458
Interviewer: How did
they take you for torture?

83
00:08:11,625 --> 00:08:14,833
The method was blindfolding, and
handcuffing with metal handcuffs

84
00:08:15,750 --> 00:08:18,875
They turn your back toward
the wall, toward the toilet

85
00:08:19,250 --> 00:08:22,958
He enters and puts a black cover
over your eyes. You cannot see anything

86
00:08:23,416 --> 00:08:30,833
He grabs you by the handcuffs behind your back, leads you,
and tells you if there is something in front to lift your foot

87
00:08:31,166 --> 00:08:35,291
Until he gets you inside, to
them, in the interrogation room

88
00:08:35,375 --> 00:08:39,125
And he goes and waits outside until you
finish interrogation, then brings you back

89
00:08:39,125 --> 00:08:42,458
Of course you walk there on your
feet, but you come back crawling

90
00:08:43,916 --> 00:08:50,375
Interviewer: Was the toilet
or bathroom inside the room?

91
00:08:50,750 --> 00:08:58,041
There was nothing called a bathroom, just a
toilet. You relieve yourself there and bathe there

92
00:08:58,416 --> 00:09:07,208
It is about half a meter, very small, with a cloth
curtain. You bathe and relieve yourself inside the toilet

93
00:09:07,791 --> 00:09:16,375
There is no such thing as a bathroom. You go out
at prayer time and pray in the same solitary cell

94
00:09:17,250 --> 00:09:19,625
On the mattress. You
cannot move right or left

95
00:09:19,875 --> 00:09:27,333
Sometimes in this solitary cell, which is two
and a half meters, they put three or four people

96
00:09:28,916 --> 00:09:33,791
Interviewer: Was <i>ludaelin</i> [dish
soap] or regular soap available?

97
00:09:34,416 --> 00:09:37,708
In the solitary cell, every
Thursday they made us clean it

98
00:09:37,791 --> 00:09:45,916
Of course they gave us cleaning supplies, then we took our
things out, he took them from us and locked the door on us

99
00:09:45,958 --> 00:09:51,041
We cleaned until it dried and then they gave us our
things back while we were inside. We never left it at all

100
00:09:52,416 --> 00:09:56,708
Interviewer: Did the toilet ever
get clogged while you were there?

101
00:09:56,875 --> 00:10:04,458
No, we never had a clogged toilet or any malfunction. Just
a water faucet and a floor drain for the toilet, that is all

102
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,750
Interviewer: Did
you have hot water?

103
00:10:07,750 --> 00:10:14,791
There was no hot water, only cold water. We never
saw hot water at all, just cold water from the faucet

